===Etymology===
From Middle English ''[[gyrle]]'' (child of either sex), of unknown origin; possibly from Old English ''*gyrele'' < Proto-Germanic ''*gurwilon-'' (diminutive of ''*gurwjoz'') < [[PIE]] ''*ghwrgh-''; another possibility is from Old English ''gierela'' ('garment').

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A female child or female young person (in contrast to ''[[boy]]'').
# Any [[woman]], regardless of her age.
# A female servant; a maid.

====Usage notes====
*Calling a grown woman a "girl" can be considered either a compliment or an insult, depending on context and sensibilities.

